Detectives have confiscated more than Sh200 million in fake US dollars, Euros and Pounds in Kileleshwa. One suspect, Bobby Kariuki Kimani, was arrested in the operation which happened on Thursday. Police carried out the operation following a tip-off. The suspect will be arraigned on Friday and charged with forgery. Police arrested five men in March believed to be members of a criminal gang engaged in printing fake currency. Close to Sh20 billion in fake money was recovered. The five were intercepted by Flying Squad officers outside Nairobiâ€™s Barclays Bank, Queensway branch.